tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE quantum_algorithms (
    algorithm_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    complexity VARCHAR(50),
    security_level VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE algorithm_parameters (
    parameter_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT,
    parameter_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    parameter_description TEXT,
    param_type VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES quantum_algorithms(algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE algorithm_parameters (
    parameter_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT NOT NULL,
    parameter_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    parameter_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    parameter_value TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES quantum_algorithms (algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE algorithm_users (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT NOT NULL,
    username VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    user_role VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    user_email VARCHAR(255),
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES quantum_algorithms (algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumAlgorithms (
    algorithm_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    author VARCHAR(100),
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumKeys (
    key_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    key_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    key_value TEXT,
    algorithm_id UUID,
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES QuantumAlgorithms (algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumAccess (
    access_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID,
    key_id UUID,
    access_level VARCHAR(50),
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES QuantumUsers (user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (key_id) REFERENCES QuantumKeys (key_id)
);

CREATE TABLE AlgorithmParameters (
    parameter_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT,
    parameter_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    parameter_value VARCHAR(255),
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES QuantumAlgorithms(algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE AlgorithmCategoryMapping (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT,
    category_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES QuantumAlgorithms(algorithm_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (category_id) REFERENCES AlgorithmCategories(category_id)
);
